# Architecture & stack

One Turborepo, **one Next.js app** (`apps/web`), route groups for public vs private. Details: @docs/ARCHITECTURE.md

```
apps/web        # Single app -> music.rajondey.com
  (public)/     # / — public home
  (private)/    # /studio, /journey, /releases — Music OS
  login/        # password gate
  api/coach/    # streaming AI (middleware-protected)
packages/tokens # design tokens (CSS vars + Tailwind preset)
packages/ui     # shared React primitives
packages/types  # shared TS types
packages/config # shared tsconfig + lint config
supabase/       # migrations (tables + RLS) + seed
```

Conventions:
- **pnpm** workspaces, **Turborepo**. Next.js 14+ App Router, **TypeScript strict**.
- **middleware.ts** protects `(private)` routes and private API; httpOnly cookie auth (WeekOS pattern).
- Public `/` never renders private session/reflection data.
- Tailwind via `packages/tokens` preset — semantic utilities, no raw hex in app code.
- Supabase writes server-side only. One Vercel deploy.
- Build phases in order; see @docs/ROADMAP.md
